Hello,
In msg.h you can read the following lines :
#define MSGMNI   128  /* <= 1k */
#define MSGMAX  4056  /* <= 4056 */
#define MSGMNB 16384  /* ? */
in other UNIX-System it is possible to allow MSGMAX doe grow to MSGMNB.
Is there any way to do so in LINUX ?
